xxl.core.predicates

Class PredicateMetaDataPredicate<P,M>

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.predicates.DecoratorPredicate<P>
      • xxl.core.predicates.PredicateMetaDataPredicate<P,M>
  • Type Parameters:
    P - the type of the predicate's parameters.
    M - the type of the meta data provided by this predicate.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    MetaDataPredicate<P,M>, Predicate<P>, Decorator<Predicate<? super P>>, MetaDataProvider<M>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LeftBind, RightBind

    public abstract class PredicateMetaDataPredicate<P,M>
extends DecoratorPredicate<P>
implements MetaDataPredicate<P,M>
    This abstract class provides a wrapper for a given predicate that provides additional meta data. The meta data of this predicate can be accessed by calling the getMetaData method. Concrete implementations of this predicate must implement the getMetaData for meta data access.
    See Also:
    DecoratorPredicate, MetaDataPredicate, Predicate
